Ana
===

Overview
--------
ana/ contains build-time analysis transforms and small workflow helpers.
It reads DatasetIO, writes EventListIO, and provides selection / snapshot
support around that path.

The main flow is:

  DatasetIO
      |
      v
  ana::build_event_list(...)
      |
      v
  EventListIO

More concretely:

  EventListBuild   --builds--> one EventListIO from one DatasetIO
  SampleDef        --stamps--> workflow-facing metadata onto DatasetIO::Sample
  snapshot         --exports-> selected EventListIO content to flat ROOT trees
  cuts             --defines-> named selection expressions used by build-time code
  channels         --classifies-> analysis-channel integers for selected events

Public surface
--------------
EventListBuild.hh
  Defines ana::BuildConfig and ana::build_event_list(...), the main
  DatasetIO -> EventListIO translation entry point.

SampleDef.hh
  Defines ana::SampleDef plus read_sample_defs(...) and
  apply_sample_defs(...), used by mk_dataset to stamp workflow metadata.

Snapshot.hh
  Defines snapshot::Spec plus snapshot::sample(...) and
  snapshot::merged(...), used for exporting selected columns to simpler ROOT
  trees for downstream training or inspection.

Local helper headers
--------------------
Cuts.hh
  Named preset selections and expression builders used during event-list
  construction.

Channels.hh
  Analysis-channel classification helpers used by downstream plotting and
  categorisation code.

Boundary notes
--------------
ana/ is not persistence and it is not systematics.
Keep file-format ownership in io/, systematic calculations in syst/, and
rendering in plot/.

The intended ana/ responsibility is:

  DatasetIO metadata + chained trees
      ->
  selection / derived columns / optional snapshots
      ->
  EventListIO
